{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846356691,"sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","part":{"id":"prt_d78b0f69c001w1cFkusgoghTvr","messageID":"msg_d78b0dca3001EQ0u8rrD6PMWSF","sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-2aa94329378b4d66a31bfa1aa22c5c8a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox lifecycle manager that handles sandbox deletion, TTL-based cleanup, idle timeout monitoring, max session duration enforcement, and integration with the Store interface for sandbox state persistence. This includes the garbage collector that runs periodically to clean up expired sandboxes.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: LifecycleManager type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `LifecycleManager` as a manager for sandbox lifecycle operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: LifecycleManager struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `LifecycleManager` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n28:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n29:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n30:   - `gcInterval time.Duration` for garbage collection interval\n31:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for stopping the manager\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewLifecycleManager constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewLifecycleManager(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, gcInterval time.Duration)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*LifecycleManager` with all fields initialized\n37: - AND `gcInterval` SHALL default to `GarbageCollectorInterval` if zero\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Store interface implementation\n42: \n43: The system SHALL implement the `Store` interface for sandbox state persistence.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: MemoryStore implementation\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n47: - **WHEN** reading the `MemoryStore` struct\n48: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n49:   - `mu sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe access\n50:   - `sandboxes map[string]*types.SandboxInfo` keyed by sessionID\n51:   - `expirationIndex map[string]time.Time` keyed by sandboxID for TTL tracking\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox method\n54: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` instance\n55: - **WHEN** calling `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n56: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be stored keyed by `sandbox.SessionID`\n57: - AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated with `sandbox.ExpiresAt`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID method\n60: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n61: - **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*types.SandboxInfo` if found\n63: - AND return `NotFoundError` if not found\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox method\n66: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n67: - **WHEN** calling `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n68: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be updated in the store\n69: - AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated if `ExpiresAt` changed\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\n72: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n73: - **WHEN** calling `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n74: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be removed from `sandboxes` map\n75: - AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from `expirationIndex` map\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: ListSandboxes method\n78: - **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n79: - **WHEN** calling `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context)`\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL return `[]*types.SandboxInfo` with all stored sandboxes\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: LifecycleManager Start method\n85: \n86: The system SHALL start the lifecycle manager with garbage collection loop.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Start begins garbage collection\n89: - **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` instance\n90: - **WHEN** calling `Start(ctx context.Context)`\n91: - **THEN** the garbage collection loop SHALL start\n92: - AND the loop SHALL run at `gcInterval` frequency\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Stop stops garbage collection\n95: - **GIVEN** a running `LifecycleManager`\n96: - **WHEN** calling `Stop()`\n97: - **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed\n98: - AND the garbage collection loop SHALL stop\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Garbage collection implementation\n103: \n104: The system SHALL implement garbage collection for expired sandboxes.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: GC checks expired sandboxes\n107: - **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` with `store` containing sandboxes\n108: - **WHEN** the garbage collection runs\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL check `expirationIndex` for expired entries\n110: - AND current time SHALL be compared against `ExpiresAt`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: GC deletes expired sandbox pod\n113: - **GIVEN** an expired sandbox in the store\n114: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n115: - **THEN** `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})` SHALL be called\n116: - AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from the store\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: GC handles multiple expired sandboxes\n119: - **GIVEN** multiple expired sandboxes in the store\n120: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n121: - **THEN** all expired sandboxes SHALL be deleted in sequence\n122: - AND errors for individual deletions SHALL be logged but not stop the loop\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: GC logs deletion activity\n125: - **GIVEN** a garbage collection deletion\n126: - **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted\n127: - **THEN** `logger.Info` SHALL be called with sandbox ID and reason\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: TTL-based cleanup\n132: \n133: The system SHALL enforce TTL-based cleanup for sandboxes.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Default TTL value\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n137: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n138: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from runtime spec\n141: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=4h`\n142: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n143: - **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from CodeInterpreter spec\n146: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `MaxSessionDuration=6h`\n147: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n148: - **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: TTL exceeded triggers deletion\n151: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` in the past\n152: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n153: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be marked for deletion\n154: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Idle timeout enforcement\n159: \n160: The system SHALL enforce idle timeout for sandboxes.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Default idle timeout value\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n164: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n165: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Idle timeout from runtime spec\n168: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=30m`\n169: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n170: - **THEN** the idle timeout SHALL be derived from `SessionTimeout`\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: LastActivity tracking\n173: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity`\n174: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n175: - **THEN** `LastActivity` SHALL be compared against current time\n176: - AND if `current - LastActivity > SessionTimeout`, sandbox SHALL be deleted\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion\n179: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with no activity for longer than `SessionTimeout`\n180: - **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n181: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be deleted\n182: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonIdleTimeout`\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxHandler implementation\n187: \n188: The system SHALL implement the sandbox deletion handler.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxHandler struct\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n192: - **WHEN** reading the handler struct\n193: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler` SHALL have method `DeleteSandbox(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: DELETE endpoint registration\n196: - **GIVEN** `SandboxHandler.Register(r chi.Router)`\n197: - **WHEN** examining registered routes\n198: - **THEN** `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` SHALL be registered\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox by name\n201: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n202: - **WHEN** processing the request\n203: - **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name using label selector\n204: - AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n207: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n208: - **WHEN** processing the request\n209: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox updates store\n212: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted via API\n213: - **WHEN** the pod deletion succeeds\n214: - **THEN** `store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox sets session-end annotation\n217: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n218: - **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n219: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n220: - AND the pod SHALL be updated with `Update` call before deletion\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox returns success\n223: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox deletion\n224: - **WHEN** writing the response\n225: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n226: - AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n227: - AND body SHALL be `SuccessResponse{Data: {\"deleted\": true, \"sandboxId\": \"<id>\"}}`\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxRequest type\n232: \n233: The system SHALL define request types for sandbox deletion API.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxRequest struct\n236: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n237: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteSandboxRequest` struct\n238: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n239:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional, can use URL path)\n240:   - `Force bool` with JSON tag `force` (optional, force delete)\n241:   - `GracePeriodSeconds int64` with JSON tag `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Session end handling\n246: \n247: The system SHALL properly handle session end transitions.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Session-end annotation on deletion\n250: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with active session\n251: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n252: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Session-end annotation format\n255: - **GIVEN** a session-end annotation being set\n256: - **WHEN** setting the annotation value\n257: - **THEN** the value SHALL be RFC3339 formatted timestamp\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Session-end updates pod before deletion\n260: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted with grace period\n261: - **WHEN** updating the pod\n262: - **THEN** the pod SHALL be updated with `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Update(ctx, pod, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n263: - AND the deletion SHALL proceed after update\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ### Requirement: NotFoundError handling\n268: \n269: The system SHALL handle not found errors for sandbox operations.\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found on delete\n272: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request for non-existent sandbox\n273: - **WHEN** processing the request\n274: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n275: - AND `Message` SHALL indicate sandbox not found\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found in store\n278: - **GIVEN** a `GetSandboxBySessionID` call for non-existent session\n279: - **WHEN** the call executes\n280: - **THEN** `NotFoundError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Name: sessionID}` SHALL be returned\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### Requirement: Force deletion\n285: \n286: The system SHALL support force deletion of sandboxes.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: Force delete bypasses grace period\n289: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with `force=true`\n290: - **WHEN** processing the request\n291: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 0\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Force delete removes finalizers\n294: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with finalizers\n295: - **WHEN** force deleting\n296: - **THEN** finalizers SHALL be removed before deletion\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### Requirement: Deletion validation\n301: \n302: The system SHALL validate deletion requests.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Name required for delete\n305: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request without name in path\n306: - **WHEN** processing the request\n307: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Lifecycle status tracking\n312: \n313: The system SHALL track sandbox lifecycle status.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: SandboxInfo status field\n316: - **GIVEN** `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n317: - **WHEN** reading `SandboxInfo`\n318: - **THEN** `Status` field SHALL be present with JSON tag `status`\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Status values\n321: - **GIVEN** sandbox lifecycle transitions\n322: - **WHEN** updating status\n323: - **THEN** valid values SHALL include:\n324:   - `\"creating\"` - sandbox being created\n325:   - `\"running\"` - sandbox active\n326:   - `\"expiring\"` - sandbox approaching TTL\n327:   - `\"idle\"` - sandbox idle timeout approaching\n328:   - `\"terminating\"` - sandbox being deleted\n329:   - `\"terminated\"` - sandbox deleted\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Status update on deletion\n332: - **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted\n333: - **WHEN** deletion begins\n334: - **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminating\"`\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Status update after deletion\n337: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deleted successfully\n338: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n339: - **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminated\"`\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: Error handling for lifecycle operations\n344: \n345: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors during lifecycle operations.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Pod deletion error\n348: - **GIVEN** a pod deletion that returns error\n349: - **WHEN** garbage collection or delete handler executes\n350: - **THEN** error SHALL be logged\n351: - AND `InternalError` SHALL be returned for API calls\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Pod update error before delete\n354: - **GIVEN** a pod update that fails before deletion\n355: - **WHEN** setting session-end annotation\n356: - **THEN** the error SHALL be logged\n357: - AND deletion SHALL proceed anyway (annotation update is non-blocking)\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ### Requirement: Concurrent deletion safety\n362: \n363: The system SHALL handle concurrent deletion requests safely.\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Same sandbox deleted concurrently\n366: - **GIVEN** two delete requests for the same sandbox\n367: - **WHEN** both requests execute\n368: - **THEN** only one SHALL succeed\n369: - AND the second SHALL receive 404 Not Found or 409 Conflict\n370: \n371: #### Scenario: Store deletion thread safety\n372: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with concurrent operations\n373: - **WHEN** multiple goroutines access the store\n374: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL protect all map operations\n375: \n376: ---\n377: \n378: ### Requirement: GC interval configuration\n379: \n380: The system SHALL allow configurable garbage collection interval.\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Default GC interval\n383: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n384: - **WHEN** reading the constants\n385: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Custom GC interval\n388: - **GIVEN** `NewLifecycleManager` with `gcInterval=5m`\n389: - **WHEN** creating the manager\n390: - **THEN** garbage collection SHALL run every 5 minutes\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Unit tests for LifecycleManager\n395: \n396: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for lifecycle management.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: LifecycleManager creation test\n399: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n400: - **WHEN** running tests\n401: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n402:   - NewLifecycleManager returns valid instance\n403:   - Default gcInterval is applied\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: GC loop test\n406: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n407: - **WHEN** running tests\n408: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n409:   - Start begins the GC loop\n410:   - Stop terminates the GC loop\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: TTL cleanup test\n413: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n414: - **WHEN** running tests\n415: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n416:   - Expired sandboxes are detected\n417:   - Expired sandboxes are deleted from store and Kubernetes\n418: \n419: #### Scenario: Idle timeout test\n420: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n421: - **WHEN** running tests\n422: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n423:   - Idle sandboxes are detected\n424:   - Idle sandboxes are deleted\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ### Requirement: Unit tests for MemoryStore\n429: \n430: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for MemoryStore.\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: Store CRUD test\n433: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n434: - **WHEN** running tests\n435: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n436:   - StoreSandbox stores sandbox correctly\n437:   - GetSandboxBySessionID returns correct sandbox\n438:   - UpdateSandbox updates sandbox correctly\n439:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n440:   - ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Store concurrency test\n443: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n444: - **WHEN** running tests\n445: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n446:   - Concurrent StoreSandbox operations are safe\n447:   - Concurrent Get and Delete operations are safe\n448: \n449: #### Scenario: NotFound error test\n450: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n451: - **WHEN** running tests\n452: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n453:   - GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### Requirement: Unit tests for DeleteSandbox handler\n458: \n459: The system SHALL have unit tests for sandbox deletion handler.\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox success test\n462: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n463: - **WHEN** running tests\n464: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n465:   - DELETE returns 200 on success\n466:   - Pod is deleted from Kubernetes\n467:   - Sandbox is removed from store\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox not found test\n470: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n471: - **WHEN** running tests\n472: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n473:   - DELETE returns 404 for non-existent sandbox\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Grace period test\n476: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n477: - **WHEN** running tests\n478: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n479:   - GracePeriodSeconds is applied to DeleteOptions\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Force delete test\n482: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n483: - **WHEN** running tests\n484: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n485:   - Force=true sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n486: \n487: ---\n488: \n489: ### Requirement: Integration tests for lifecycle\n490: \n491: The system SHALL have integration tests for lifecycle management.\n492: \n493: #### Scenario: Full lifecycle flow test\n494: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n495: - **WHEN** running tests\n496: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n497:   - Sandbox creation stores in MemoryStore\n498:   - TTL expiration triggers deletion\n499:   - Store reflects deleted sandbox\n500: \n501: #### Scenario: Concurrent lifecycle test\n502: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n503: - **WHEN** running tests\n504: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n505:   - Multiple sandboxes handled concurrently\n506:   - No race conditions\n507: \n508: ---\n509: \n510: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n511: \n512: The system SHALL organize lifecycle files correctly.\n513: \n514: #### Scenario: Lifecycle file location\n515: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n516: - **WHEN** listing files\n517: - **THEN** `lifecycle.go` SHALL exist with `LifecycleManager` implementation\n518: \n519: #### Scenario: Lifecycle test file location\n520: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n521: - **WHEN** listing files\n522: - **THEN** `lifecycle_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Store file location\n525: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n526: - **WHEN** listing files\n527: - **THEN** `store.go` SHALL exist with `MemoryStore` implementation\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: Store test file location\n530: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n531: - **WHEN** listing files\n532: - **THEN** `store_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## Implementation Files\n537: \n538: | File | Purpose |\n539: |------|---------|\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | LifecycleManager implementation |\n541: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go` | LifecycleManager unit tests |\n542: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | MemoryStore implementation |\n543: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go` | MemoryStore unit tests |\n544: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | DeleteSandbox handler (extends AR-005) |\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## Dependencies\n549: \n550: | Package | Purpose |\n551: |---------|---------|\n552: | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n553: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n554: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n555: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, DeleteOptions |\n556: | `sync` | Thread-safe store operations |\n557: | `time` | TTL and interval handling |\n558: | `context` | Context propagation |\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## API Endpoints\n563: \n564: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n565: |----------|--------|---------|\n566: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox by name |\n567: \n568: ---\n569: \n570: ## Error Codes\n571: \n572: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n573: |------|-------------|-------------|\n574: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Missing or invalid parameters |\n575: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox not found |\n576: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n577: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Lifecycle manager not running |\n578: \n579: ---\n580: \n581: ## Deletion Reasons\n582: \n583: | Reason | Description |\n584: |--------|-------------|\n585: | `IdleTimeout` | Sandbox deleted due to idle timeout exceeded |\n586: | `MaxDurationReached` | Sandbox deleted due to max session duration exceeded |\n587: | `UserRequest` | Sandbox deleted via DELETE API request |\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## Annotation Keys for Lifecycle\n592: \n593: | Key | Value Source |\n594: |-----|--------------|\n595: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp on deletion |\n596: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Updated on each activity |\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## Sandbox Status Values\n601: \n602: | Status | Description |\n603: |--------|-------------|\n604: | `creating` | Sandbox pod being created |\n605: | `running` | Sandbox active and serving |\n606: | `expiring` | Approaching TTL expiration |\n607: | `idle` | Approaching idle timeout |\n608: | `terminating` | Sandbox being deleted |\n609: | `terminated` | Sandbox deleted |\n610: \n611: ---\n612: \n613: ## Validation Checklist\n614: \n615: - [ ] LifecycleManager struct defined with all required fields\n616: - [ ] NewLifecycleManager constructor initializes all fields\n617: - [ ] MemoryStore implements Store interface\n618: - [ ] StoreSandbox stores sandbox keyed by sessionID\n619: - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox or NotFoundError\n620: - [ ] UpdateSandbox updates sandbox and expiration index\n621: - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from both maps\n622: - [ ] ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n623: - [ ] Start begins garbage collection loop\n624: - [ ] Stop terminates garbage collection loop\n625: - [ ] GC checks expirationIndex for expired entries\n626: - [ ] TTL exceeded triggers deletion with MaxDurationReached reason\n627: - [ ] Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion with IdleTimeout reason\n628: - [ ] DELETE endpoint registered at `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n629: - [ ] GracePeriodSeconds query parameter applied\n630: - [ ] Force delete sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n631: - [ ] Session-end annotation set before deletion\n632: - [ ] Store updated on successful deletion\n633: - [ ] NotFound handling for missing sandbox\n634: - [ ] Concurrent deletion handled safely\n635: - [ ] Status tracking for lifecycle transitions\n636: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n637: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n638: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n639: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 639 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox lifecycle manager that handles sandbox deletion, TTL-based cleanup, idle timeout monitoring, max session duration enforcement, and integration with the Store interface for sandbox state persistence. This includes the garbage collector that runs periodically to clean up expired sandboxes.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: LifecycleManager type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `LifecycleManager` as a manager for sandbox lifecycle operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775846356667,"end":1775846356688}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775846356718,"sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","part":{"id":"prt_d78b0f6d2001vtJRjcpkHq43MK","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78b0dca3001EQ0u8rrD6PMWSF","sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23242,"input":4605,"output":187,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18450}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775846359807,"sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","part":{"id":"prt_d78b102fb001DA11fKEhvt4alM","messageID":"msg_d78b0f706001iwwZXAqg72Wwj2","sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846367212,"sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","part":{"id":"prt_d78b1123a0012zhe2vZ5saGwY5","messageID":"msg_d78b0f706001iwwZXAqg72Wwj2","sessionID":"ses_2874f57d1ffeEsMYFU1BdtJMgP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fb63c3a007154ca393cea78d03d368ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: SandboxHandler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxHandler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n28:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: NewSandboxHandler constructor\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n32: - **WHEN** calling `NewSandboxHandler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, logger Logger, namespace string)`\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*SandboxHandler` with all fields initialized\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Handler registration interface\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement `Handler` interface for route registration.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Handler interface implementation\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n43: - **WHEN** examining `SandboxHandler`\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method from `workloadmanager.Handler` interface\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Register method routes\n47: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxHandler` instance\n48: - **WHEN** calling `Register(r chi.Router)`\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL register the following routes:\n50:   - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox creation\n51:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox retrieval\n52:   - `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox deletion\n53:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox listing\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: CreateSandboxRequest type definition\n58: \n59: The system SHALL define request types for sandbox creation API.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest struct definition\n62: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n63: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateSandboxRequest` struct\n64: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n65:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (required)\n66:   - `RuntimeName string` with JSON tag `runtimeName` (required)\n67:   - `RuntimeKind string` with JSON tag `runtimeKind` (required, enum: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n68:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId` (optional)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: RuntimeKind validation\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n72: - **WHEN** examining the `RuntimeKind` field\n73: - **THEN** valid values SHALL be `\"AgentRuntime\"` and `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: SandboxResponse type definition\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define response types for sandbox API.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: SandboxResponse struct definition\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n83: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxResponse` struct\n84: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n85:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name`\n86:   - `PodName string` with JSON tag `podName`\n87:   - `Namespace string` with JSON tag `namespace`\n88:   - `Status string` with JSON tag `status`\n89:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId`\n90:   - `CreatedAt time.Time` with JSON tag `createdAt`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: SandboxListResponse struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxListResponse` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain field `Items []SandboxResponse` with JSON tag `items`\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation logic\n100: \n101: The system SHALL create Kubernetes Pods based on AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter templates.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime spec\n104: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"AgentRuntime\"`\n105: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n106: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the AgentRuntime\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter spec\n109: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n110: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n111: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the CodeInterpreter\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Pod creation from AgentRuntime template\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime spec with `Template *SandboxTemplate`\n115: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n116: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n117: - AND the Pod's `Spec` SHALL be derived from `AgentRuntime.Spec.Template.Spec`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Pod creation from CodeInterpreter template\n120: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter spec with `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n121: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n122: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n123: - AND the Pod's container image SHALL be from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template.Image`\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### Requirement: Label application\n128: \n129: The system SHALL apply required labels to sandbox pods according to shared_types.go constants.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Owner runtime label\n132: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n133: - **WHEN** applying labels\n134: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` SHALL be set to the runtime name\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Owner kind label\n137: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n138: - **WHEN** applying labels\n139: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` SHALL be set to `RuntimeKind` value\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for AgentRuntime\n142: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for AgentRuntime\n143: - **WHEN** applying labels\n144: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"agent\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for CodeInterpreter\n147: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for CodeInterpreter\n148: - **WHEN** applying labels\n149: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"code-interpreter\"`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Session ID label\n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created with `SessionID`\n153: - **WHEN** applying labels\n154: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` SHALL be set to the session ID\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Merge template labels\n157: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template labels\n158: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n159: - **THEN** template labels SHALL be merged with system labels\n160: - AND system labels SHALL not be overridden by template labels\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### Requirement: Annotation application\n165: \n166: The system SHALL apply required annotations to sandbox pods.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Session start annotation\n169: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n170: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n171: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set to current timestamp in RFC3339 format\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Last activity annotation\n174: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n175: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n176: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Auth mode annotation for CodeInterpreter\n179: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod being created\n180: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n181: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` SHALL be set to `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Merge template annotations\n184: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template annotations\n185: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n186: - **THEN** template annotations SHALL be merged with system annotations\n187: - AND system annotations SHALL not be overridden by template annotations\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Pod naming convention\n192: \n193: The system SHALL generate unique pod names for sandboxes.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Pod name format\n196: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `Name=\"my-sandbox\"`\n197: - **WHEN** generating the pod name\n198: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL follow format `{sandbox-name}-{randomSuffix}`\n199: - AND the random suffix SHALL be 5 characters alphanumeric\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Pod name uniqueness\n202: - **GIVEN** an existing pod with the same sandbox name\n203: - **WHEN** creating a new sandbox\n204: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL be unique due to random suffix\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Validation error handling\n209: \n210: The system SHALL validate request parameters and return appropriate errors.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Missing name validation\n213: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `Name`\n214: - **WHEN** processing the request\n215: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n216: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"name\"`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Missing runtimeName validation\n219: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `RuntimeName`\n220: - **WHEN** processing the request\n221: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n222: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeName\"`\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Invalid RuntimeKind validation\n225: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n226: - **WHEN** processing the request\n227: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n228: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeKind\"`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Runtime not found\n231: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with non-existent `RuntimeName`\n232: - **WHEN** processing the request\n233: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Requirement: Sandbox retrieval\n238: \n239: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox pod information.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Get sandbox by name\n242: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n243: - **WHEN** processing the request\n244: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n245: - AND return `SandboxResponse` for the matching pod\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found\n248: - **GIVEN** a GET request for a non-existent sandbox\n249: - **WHEN** processing the request\n250: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: List sandboxes\n253: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n254: - **WHEN** processing the request\n255: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list all pods with label selector containing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type`\n256: - AND return `SandboxListResponse` with all matching pods\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: List sandboxes by runtime\n259: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes?runtimeName={runtimeName}`\n260: - **WHEN** processing the request\n261: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Sandbox deletion\n266: \n267: The system SHALL delete sandbox pods.\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox\n270: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n271: - **WHEN** processing the request\n272: - **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name\n273: - AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n276: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n277: - **WHEN** processing the request\n278: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion updates session annotation\n281: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n282: - **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n283: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n284: - AND the pod SHALL be updated before deletion\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ### Requirement: Warm pool handling for CodeInterpreter\n289: \n290: The system SHALL support warm pool management for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Check warm pool availability\n293: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n294: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n295: - **THEN** the handler SHALL check for available warm pool pods with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member=true`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Use warm pool pod\n298: - **GIVEN** an available warm pool pod exists\n299: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n300: - **THEN** the handler SHALL update the warm pool pod instead of creating a new pod\n301: - AND remove `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` annotation\n302: - AND set `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` label\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod not available\n305: - **GIVEN** no warm pool pod is available\n306: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n307: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a new pod normally\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Warm pool annotation for new pods\n310: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod created outside warm pool usage\n311: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n312: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` SHALL NOT be set\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### Requirement: Port configuration\n317: \n318: The system SHALL configure container ports based on TargetPort definitions.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Add container ports\n321: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `Spec.Ports []TargetPort`\n322: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n323: - **THEN** each `TargetPort` SHALL be mapped to a `corev1.ContainerPort` in the pod spec\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Port name from TargetPort\n326: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name=\"http\"`\n327: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n328: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.Name` SHALL be set to `\"http\"`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Port number from TargetPort\n331: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Port=8080`\n332: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n333: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.ContainerPort` SHALL be set to `8080`\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: RuntimeClassName handling\n338: \n339: The system SHALL apply RuntimeClassName for sandbox pods.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName from CodeInterpreter template\n342: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName=\" KataContainers\"`\n343: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n344: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL be set to `\"KataContainers\"`\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName nil handling\n347: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName` nil\n348: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n349: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL NOT be set\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Image configuration for CodeInterpreter\n354: \n355: The system SHALL configure container image for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Image from template\n358: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Image=\"python:3.11\"`\n359: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n360: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `\"python:3.11\"`\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ImagePullPolicy from template\n363: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullPolicy=\"Always\"`\n364: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n365: - **THEN** the container `ImagePullPolicy` SHALL be `corev1.PullPolicy(\"Always\")`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets from template\n368: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullSecrets`\n369: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n370: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.ImagePullSecrets` SHALL be set from template\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### Requirement: Environment variables handling\n375: \n376: The system SHALL apply environment variables from template.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Environment variables from CodeInterpreter template\n379: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Environment []corev1.EnvVar`\n380: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n381: - **THEN** the container `Env` SHALL include all environment variables from template\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: Environment variables merge\n384: - **GIVEN** system environment variables and template environment variables\n385: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n386: - **THEN** template environment variables SHALL be appended after system environment variables\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Resource requirements handling\n391: \n392: The system SHALL apply resource requirements from template.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Resources from CodeInterpreter template\n395: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Resources` containing limits and requests\n396: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n397: - **THEN** the container `Resources` SHALL be set from template\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Default resources when not specified\n400: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Template.Resources`\n401: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n402: - **THEN** default resource limits SHALL NOT be applied (let Kubernetes defaults apply)\n403: \n404: ---\n405: \n406: ### Requirement: Command and Args handling\n407: \n408: The system SHALL apply command and args from template.\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: Command from template\n411: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Command=[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n412: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n413: - **THEN** the container `Command` SHALL be set to `[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Args from template\n416: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Args=[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n417: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n418: - **THEN** the container `Args` SHALL be set to `[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Empty Command and Args\n421: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Command` and `Args`\n422: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n423: - **THEN** the container SHALL use the default entrypoint from the image\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ### Requirement: Session management\n428: \n429: The system SHALL manage session lifecycle annotations.\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Session start timestamp\n432: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for a session\n433: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n434: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Session timeout calculation\n437: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=15m`\n438: - **WHEN** calculating session expiration\n439: - **THEN** the expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + SessionTimeout`\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: Max session duration calculation\n442: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=8h`\n443: - **WHEN** calculating maximum session expiration\n444: - **THEN** the maximum expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + MaxSessionDuration`\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ### Requirement: Error handling and responses\n449: \n450: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors appropriately.\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API error\n453: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns an error\n454: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox request\n455: - **THEN** the error SHALL be wrapped in `InternalError`\n456: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"INTERNAL_ERROR\"`\n457: \n458: #### Scenario: Pod already exists\n459: - **GIVEN** a pod with the same name already exists\n460: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n461: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 409 Conflict\n462: - AND `ErrorResponse.Code` SHALL be `\"CONFLICT\"`\n463: \n464: #### Scenario: Namespace not found\n465: - **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n466: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n467: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Request context usage\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use request context for API calls.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Context propagation\n476: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with context\n477: - **WHEN** making Kubernetes API calls\n478: - **THEN** `r.Context()` SHALL be used as the context parameter\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Context timeout handling\n481: - **GIVEN** a request context that times out\n482: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API call is in progress\n483: - **THEN** the API call SHALL be cancelled\n484: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 503 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ### Requirement: JSON request parsing\n489: \n490: The system SHALL parse JSON request body correctly.\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: Valid JSON parsing\n493: - **GIVEN** a POST request with valid JSON body\n494: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n495: - **THEN** `json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&req)` SHALL be used\n496: - AND request body SHALL be closed\n497: \n498: #### Scenario: Invalid JSON parsing\n499: - **GIVEN** a POST request with invalid JSON body\n500: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n501: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n502: - AND `Details.reason` SHALL indicate JSON parsing failure\n503: \n504: ---\n505: \n506: ### Requirement: JSON response writing\n507: \n508: The system SHALL write JSON responses correctly.\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: Success response\n511: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox creation\n512: - **WHEN** writing the response\n513: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 201 Created\n514: - AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n515: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxResponse` JSON\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: List response\n518: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox list\n519: - **WHEN** writing the response\n520: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n521: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxListResponse` JSON\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ### Requirement: Unit tests\n526: \n527: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SandboxHandler.\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest validation tests\n530: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n531: - **WHEN** running tests\n532: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n533:   - Missing name returns 400\n534:   - Missing runtimeName returns 400\n535:   - Invalid RuntimeKind returns 400\n536:   - Valid request passes validation\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: Label application tests\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Owner runtime label is applied\n543:   - Owner kind label is applied\n544:   - Sandbox type label is correct for AgentRuntime\n545:   - Sandbox type label is correct for CodeInterpreter\n546:   - Template labels are merged correctly\n547: \n548: #### Scenario: Annotation application tests\n549: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n550: - **WHEN** running tests\n551: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n552:   - Session start annotation is applied\n553:   - Last activity annotation is applied\n554:   - Auth mode annotation is applied for CodeInterpreter\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: Pod creation tests\n557: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n558: - **WHEN** running tests\n559: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n560:   - Pod is created with correct spec from AgentRuntime template\n561:   - Pod is created with correct spec from CodeInterpreter template\n562:   - Pod name follows naming convention\n563: \n564: #### Scenario: Warm pool tests\n565: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n566: - **WHEN** running tests\n567: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n568:   - Warm pool pod is reused when available\n569:   - New pod is created when warm pool not available\n570:   - Warm pool annotation is removed on reuse\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Integration tests\n575: \n576: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake Kubernetes clients.\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Full sandbox creation flow\n579: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n580: - **WHEN** running integration tests\n581: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify complete sandbox creation from request to pod creation\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: End-to-end API test\n584: - **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer with SandboxHandler\n585: - **WHEN** sending POST request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify correct HTTP response and pod creation\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n591: \n592: The system SHALL organize sandbox handler files correctly.\n593: \n594: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler file location\n595: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n596: - **WHEN** listing files\n597: - **THEN** `sandbox.go` SHALL exist with `SandboxHandler` implementation\n598: \n599: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler test file location\n600: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n601: - **WHEN** listing files\n602: - **THEN** `sandbox_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n603: \n604: ---\n605: \n606: ## Implementation Files\n607: \n608: | File | Purpose |\n609: |------|---------|\n610: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | SandboxHandler implementation |\n611: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go` | SandboxHandler unit tests |\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: ## Dependencies\n616: \n617: | Package | Purpose |\n618: |---------|---------|\n619: | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n620: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n621: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod, Container types |\n622: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, ListOptions, CreateOptions |\n623: | `encoding/json` | Request/Response JSON handling |\n624: | `time` | Timestamp handling for annotations |\n625: \n626: ---\n627: \n628: ## API Endpoints\n629: \n630: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n631: |----------|--------|---------|\n632: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | POST | Create a new sandbox |\n633: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | GET | Get sandbox by name |\n634: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n635: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | GET | List sandboxes |\n636: \n637: ---\n638: \n639: ## Error Codes\n640: \n641: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n642: |------|-------------|-------------|\n643: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Invalid request parameter |\n644: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Runtime or sandbox not found |\n645: | `CONFLICT` | 409 | Pod already exists |\n646: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n647: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Context timeout or dependency unavailable |\n648: \n649: ---\n650: \n651: ## Label Keys Applied\n652: \n653: | Key | Value Source |\n654: |-----|--------------|\n655: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `RuntimeName` from request |\n656: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `RuntimeKind` from request |\n657: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"agent\"` or `\"code-interpreter\"` |\n658: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | `SessionID` from request |\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: ## Annotation Keys Applied\n663: \n664: | Key | Value Source |\n665: |-----|--------------|\n666: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` | Current timestamp RFC3339 |\n667: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Current timestamp |\n668: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` | `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode` |\n669: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp (on deletion) |\n670: \n671: ---\n672: \n673: ## Validation Checklist\n674: \n675: - [ ] SandboxHandler implements Handler interface\n676: - [ ] POST `/api/v1/sandboxes` creates pods correctly\n677: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` retrieves sandbox info\n678: - [ ] DELETE `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` deletes sandbox pod\n679: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes` lists all sandboxes\n680: - [ ] Labels are applied according to shared_types.go constants\n681: - [ ] Annotations are applied correctly\n682: - [ ] Warm pool handling works for CodeInterpreter\n683: - [ ] Port configuration from TargetPort\n684: - [ ] RuntimeClassName handling\n685: - [ ] Environment variables from template\n686: - [ ] Resource requirements from template\n687: - [ ] Command and Args from template\n688: - [ ] Validation errors return correct HTTP status\n689: - [ ] Kubernetes API errors handled correctly\n690: - [ ] Context propagated to API calls\n691: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n692: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n693: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n694: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 694 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775846367189,"end":1775846367209}}}}
